    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nPlugins may [want to handle file args](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35448#issuecomment-3315105002) passed at startup. But some plugins rename some of those, e.g. Oil renames directory args to `oil://...`. Also, the \"argument list\" can be modified by plugins in other ways.\n\nThus, `vim.fn.argv()` does not give a reliable view of which files were opened at startup.\n\nMeanwhile, `v:arg` includes all startup args, not only \"file\" args, and it's non-trivial for a plugin to know which of those are file args.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIntroduce `v:argf` so plugins know exactly what \"file args\" were given at startup.\n\n(Or, remind me of another way to do this, if I forgot :)",
